Lab: Unprotected admin functionality

Vulnerability: Unprotected admin panel.

Objective: To access admin panel and delete the user carlos.

Exploitation Steps:
1. Open the lab, go to the URL and manually add /robots.txt at the end of the URL.
2. This will open robots.txt file which contains -
     User-agent: *
     Disallow: /adiministrator-panel
3. The Disallow entry revealed the hidden admin panel path.
4. Now go back to URL and replace /robots.txt with /administrator-panel.
5. The admin panel opened without any authentication.
6. Delete the user carlos.

How it works:
- robots.txt file is used by websites to tell search engines which paths should not be indexed. We can access it by using /robots.txt at the end of URL.
- Developers sometimes store sensitive paths inside this file, assuming users will not check it.
- In this case the path to access admin panel was stored in it whcih was /administrator-panel.
- By appending it to the URL one can easily access admin panel as there is no authentication.

Result: The admin panel was accessed without any authentication and we were able to delete the user carlos.

Risk Involved: An attacker may discover hidden administrative paths or endpoints and gain unauthorized access to sensitive features.

Remediation:
-Do not expose sensitive paths inside robots.txt.
-Implement proper authentication and access control for admin panels.
-Restrict unauthorized users from accessing administrative functionality.
